HEADWORD: Castilian
<hw>Cas*til"ian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>castellano</ets>, from <ets>Castila</ets>, NL. <ets>Castilia</ets>,
<ets>Castella</ets>. Castile, which received its name from the castles
erected on the frontiers as a barrier against the Moors.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>An inhabitant or native of Castile, in Spain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The Spanish language as spoken in Castile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castillan</ent>⟦br⟧
